					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13445160#post-4701118</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13445160/scp-5955#post-4701118</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 26 Jun 2020 10:54:35 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Yasha277</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1835799</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Definitely could be better if the whole environmental message wasn't so&#8230; obvious. The ending had real potential to elicit emotional reactions, but there wasn't enough build-up and too much was put into rubbing environmentalism in my face.<br /> On a different note, I feel we really need a bit more description on its appearance. Sure, you say it's a sphere of flesh, but then you proceed to talk about its posterior, anterior etc.. if it has these features, then it must be more than just a uniform sphere.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13445160#post-4698006</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13445160/scp-5955#post-4698006</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 23 Jun 2020 19:47:07 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TheMightyMcB</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4483018</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>No, I totally got that part. My main issue was that the actual words that the anomaly spelled out were super heavy-handed. They practically beat the reader over the head with &quot;I am trying to help and you are killing me&quot;.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
